1
00:01:52,519 --> 00:01:54,688
You're a brilliant woman,
Lieutenant.

2
00:01:54,771 --> 00:01:57,273
So why would you
try something so stupid?

3
00:01:57,357 --> 00:02:01,236
I was wrong.
I have to answer for that.

4
00:02:01,319 --> 00:02:03,029
Huh?

5
00:02:03,113 --> 00:02:05,115
Let's get moving, ma'am.

6
00:02:06,533 --> 00:02:08,535
[NIIMI]
Thank you for the help.

7
00:02:14,207 --> 00:02:17,210
Doctor. Do you think Lieutenant
Mori's an Iscandarian,

8
00:02:17,293 --> 00:02:18,420
like they said?

9
00:02:18,503 --> 00:02:21,131
That's the dumbest thing
I've heard all day.

10
00:02:31,850 --> 00:02:34,269
[HIJIKATA] This was her final
message to her sister

11
00:02:34,352 --> 00:02:36,354
as she entrusted her
with a dangerous mission

12
00:02:36,438 --> 00:02:39,315
across the stars.

13
00:02:39,399 --> 00:02:41,276
Some things I can't
explain now may become

14
00:02:41,359 --> 00:02:46,072
more clear on your journey.
Just don't lose hope.

15
00:02:46,156 --> 00:02:50,076
Stay safe out there.
And come back in one piece.

16
00:02:51,494 --> 00:02:52,996
[STARSHA]
The ultimate salvation of

17
00:02:53,079 --> 00:02:55,707
all intelligent life-forms
in the universe.

18
00:02:55,790 --> 00:02:59,252
That is the true meaning
of the "path to Iscandar."

19
00:02:59,336 --> 00:03:01,629
After all our various setbacks,
we're now 35 days

20
00:03:01,713 --> 00:03:04,049
behind schedule for getting
back to Earth on time.

21
00:03:04,132 --> 00:03:07,469
However, if the intel
from Beemela-Four is true,

22
00:03:07,552 --> 00:03:09,679
we can use this subspace
gate to instantly jump

23
00:03:09,763 --> 00:03:12,432
30,000 light-years.

24
00:03:12,515 --> 00:03:14,976
According to the data, there's
a system satellite nearby

25
00:03:15,060 --> 00:03:16,603
that controls the gate.

26
00:03:16,686 --> 00:03:19,689
The real question is can we find
a way to hijack the satellite.

27
00:03:19,773 --> 00:03:21,024
[OKITA]
Mm.

28
00:03:21,107 --> 00:03:22,984
The Wave Motion Core we
recovered contains records

29
00:03:23,068 --> 00:03:25,820
of two different alien races
involved with the gate.

30
00:03:25,904 --> 00:03:28,031
One that originally built it,
and a second race

31
00:03:28,114 --> 00:03:30,408
that controls the system now.

32
00:03:30,492 --> 00:03:31,951
Who controls it?

33
00:03:32,035 --> 00:03:34,537
[SANADA] That took some digging,
but we finally found a name.

34
00:03:34,621 --> 00:03:37,749
All right, enough suspense--
tell us who they are.

35
00:03:37,832 --> 00:03:39,793
It's the Gamilans.

36
00:03:44,089 --> 00:03:47,050
[DOMEL] I was seconds away
from destroying the <i>Yamato</i> .

37
00:03:47,133 --> 00:03:50,887
Why did you recall the fleet?
What's going on?

38
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:52,847
We brought you back
because early this morning

39
00:03:52,931 --> 00:03:54,933
our supreme leader's vessel
was destroyed

40
00:03:55,016 --> 00:03:57,227
through a cowardly act
of sabotage.

41
00:03:57,310 --> 00:03:59,771
The great Lord Desler
has been assassinated.

42
00:03:59,854 --> 00:04:01,398
[gasps]

43
00:04:01,481 --> 00:04:04,109
Before the attack, only two
members of Imperial Command

44
00:04:04,192 --> 00:04:06,152
knew he would be
visiting you on Balun.

45
00:04:06,236 --> 00:04:07,654
The first was Admiral Ditz,

46
00:04:07,737 --> 00:04:09,781
our Supreme Commander
of the Astrofleets.

47
00:04:09,864 --> 00:04:12,534
And the other
was yourself, General.

48
00:04:13,326 --> 00:04:15,286
You are here in manacles
because I'm accusing you

49
00:04:15,370 --> 00:04:17,455
of plotting our leader's
assassination.

50
00:04:17,539 --> 00:04:19,040
Are you mad?

51
00:04:19,124 --> 00:04:21,626
[GIMLEH] You and Ditz conspired
together to murder Lord Desler

52
00:04:21,710 --> 00:04:25,588
and seize control of the Empire.
Do you dare deny it?

53
00:04:25,672 --> 00:04:27,590
I don't have time
for these fantasies.

54
00:04:27,674 --> 00:04:29,884
Fantasies? You think so?

55
00:04:29,968 --> 00:04:32,971
And is your wife's arrest
for treason a fantasy as well?

56
00:04:33,054 --> 00:04:35,390
What, Elisa? What are
you talking about--

57
00:04:35,473 --> 00:04:36,891
what has she done?

58
00:04:36,975 --> 00:04:39,561
[GIMLEH] You didn't know?
She's been caught red-handed

59
00:04:39,644 --> 00:04:41,730
supporting
anti-government rebels.

60
00:04:41,813 --> 00:04:43,481
[DOMEL]
There must be some mistake!

61
00:04:43,565 --> 00:04:45,859
[GIMLEH]
That's what they all say.

62
00:04:45,942 --> 00:04:48,153
Order is the foundation
of empire,

63
00:04:48,236 --> 00:04:50,572
and it must be maintained
above all else.

64
00:04:50,655 --> 00:04:52,323
That means those
suspected of wrongdoing

65
00:04:52,407 --> 00:04:53,783
must be judged swiftly.

66
00:04:53,867 --> 00:04:55,827
No matter how
high they've climbed.

67
00:04:55,910 --> 00:04:57,454
Gimleh.

68
00:04:57,537 --> 00:04:59,080
[GIMLEH]
Hm.

69
00:04:59,164 --> 00:05:01,916
[HYSS] We shall take a vote.
Gentlemen of the jury?

70
00:05:03,376 --> 00:05:07,297
[GAMILAS MAGISTRATES]
Death!

71
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:09,674
By unanimous verdict,
the tribunal sentences

72
00:05:09,758 --> 00:05:11,801
General Domel to death
for the assassination

73
00:05:11,885 --> 00:05:13,511
of our Supreme Lord.

74
00:05:15,638 --> 00:05:19,726
[ZOELLIK laughing]

75
00:05:19,809 --> 00:05:22,270
Sir. Preparations for
naval review are complete

76
00:05:22,354 --> 00:05:23,772
and we are ready to embark.

77
00:05:23,855 --> 00:05:25,774
I take it something
good has happened?

78
00:05:25,857 --> 00:05:29,319
The tribunal has just given
Elk Domel a death sentence.

79
00:05:29,402 --> 00:05:31,571
[VANDEVEL]
Congratulations, sir!

80
00:05:31,654 --> 00:05:34,240
[laughing]

81
00:05:34,324 --> 00:05:36,159
Inform the fleet
we're launching now!

82
00:05:36,242 --> 00:05:38,620
Set course for planet Balun!

83
00:05:38,703 --> 00:05:43,708
♪

84
00:05:56,012 --> 00:05:57,931
[IMPERIAL GUARD 17B]
All right, scum, keep moving.

85
00:05:58,014 --> 00:05:59,349
[IMPERIAL GUARD 17A]
No talking.

86
00:05:59,432 --> 00:06:01,309
Eyes down. Stay in line!

87
00:06:02,977 --> 00:06:04,604
[IMPERIAL GUARD 17B]
Stop!

88
00:06:04,688 --> 00:06:06,439
--[MALE REBEL 17A grunts]
--[IMPERIAL GUARD 17C groans]

89
00:06:07,691 --> 00:06:09,442
[IMPERIAL GUARD 17A]
Uh!

90
00:06:09,526 --> 00:06:10,694
[groans]

91
00:06:10,777 --> 00:06:12,195
[gasps]

92
00:06:15,573 --> 00:06:16,908
[IMPERIAL GUARD 17B]
Get up.

93
00:06:16,991 --> 00:06:18,868
[MALE ASTROPORT PA VOICE 17A]
There's your example.

94
00:06:18,952 --> 00:06:21,329
Anyone attempting to run
will be shot on the spot.

95
00:06:33,383 --> 00:06:34,759
[LARKIN]
That the one?

96
00:06:34,843 --> 00:06:36,553
[DOLMEN]
Yeah.

97
00:06:41,766 --> 00:06:43,643
[KITANO]
<i>That's</i> the subspace gate?

98
00:06:43,727 --> 00:06:45,729
[NANBU]
Hardly looks functional.

99
00:06:45,812 --> 00:06:47,355
So do you really think
it can transport us

100
00:06:47,439 --> 00:06:49,941
30,000 light-years
in a single warp?

101
00:06:50,025 --> 00:06:52,986
[MISAKI]
Yes it can.

102
00:06:53,069 --> 00:06:55,071
[DR. SADO]
No. There's no way.

103
00:06:55,155 --> 00:06:58,241
I thought I'd seen everything
but I can't help you with this.

104
00:06:58,324 --> 00:06:59,743
If we don't
figure out something,

105
00:06:59,826 --> 00:07:02,412
at this rate it's going to
become a serious problem for us.

106
00:07:02,495 --> 00:07:05,290
My job is to take care of
the crew, not the frickin' ship!

107
00:07:05,373 --> 00:07:07,167
--I'm well aware.
--[DR. SADO] Hm.

108
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:09,461
I think I deserve
an explanation, Captain.

109
00:07:09,544 --> 00:07:12,422
It's not like you to go along
with somethin' like this.

110
00:07:12,505 --> 00:07:14,966
And keeping it a secret
from the crew?

111
00:07:15,050 --> 00:07:16,634
That's not the Okita I know.

112
00:07:16,718 --> 00:07:18,386
We had strict orders
from Central Command.

113
00:07:18,470 --> 00:07:20,430
I don't care
about orders, damn it!

114
00:07:20,513 --> 00:07:22,307
[OKITA] "You need the courage
to disobey an order

115
00:07:22,390 --> 00:07:25,310
you believe is wrong, especially
when lives are at stake.

116
00:07:25,393 --> 00:07:27,937
In war, it's the only way
you can live with yourself."

117
00:07:28,021 --> 00:07:29,439
Huh?

118
00:07:29,522 --> 00:07:32,067
I told Kodai that but haven't
lived up to my own words.

119
00:07:33,568 --> 00:07:35,570
We should've been honest
with ourselves and the crew

120
00:07:35,653 --> 00:07:37,280
about what we've done.

121
00:07:37,364 --> 00:07:41,493
X.O. I will assume
full responsibility.

122
00:07:41,576 --> 00:07:43,370
[DR. SADO]
Mmm.

123
00:07:47,624 --> 00:07:49,125
[door hisses]

124
00:07:49,209 --> 00:07:51,711
[IWATA] All I'm saying is Mori
being an alien is a huge bummer.

125
00:07:51,795 --> 00:07:54,255
Yeah, no kidding. Oh!

126
00:07:54,339 --> 00:07:57,634
I was her biggest fan,
but I guess she's--

127
00:07:57,717 --> 00:08:00,637
Sir! The Type One-Hundred is
fueled and ready to go, sir!

128
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,389
Good, thanks.

129
00:08:09,270 --> 00:08:11,064
I'm ready to go.

130
00:08:20,573 --> 00:08:23,076
[AIHARA] I know Kodai's flying
and going for protection,

131
00:08:23,159 --> 00:08:25,745
but why do you think
the X.O. would take Mori?

132
00:08:25,829 --> 00:08:28,331
I don't know, maybe because
she's an Iscandarian?

133
00:08:28,415 --> 00:08:30,417
Hey! She's not an alien, okay?

134
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:32,085
But how else do you
explain her having

135
00:08:32,168 --> 00:08:33,962
a private message from Starsha?

136
00:08:34,045 --> 00:08:36,089
And she only remembers
a year before we launched.

137
00:08:36,172 --> 00:08:37,173
It does fit.

138
00:08:37,257 --> 00:08:38,341
That's all just speculation!

139
00:08:38,425 --> 00:08:39,634
We're in the middle
of a mission here.

140
00:08:39,718 --> 00:08:41,886
Cut the chatter, crewmen!

141
00:08:41,970 --> 00:08:45,181
[SAIJO] Type One-Hundred has
landed on system satellite, sir.

142
00:08:47,976 --> 00:08:54,733
[clinking]

143
00:08:54,816 --> 00:08:57,193
[SANADA] I don't see any
evidence of booby traps.

144
00:08:59,070 --> 00:09:00,488
Looks like it was
used as a base,

145
00:09:00,572 --> 00:09:02,365
but it's been abandoned
a long time.

146
00:09:02,449 --> 00:09:05,118
The inertial mass system
is online, though,

147
00:09:05,201 --> 00:09:07,454
so the rest is most likely
still functional.

148
00:09:07,537 --> 00:09:09,706
This fighter could be
useful to us in the future.

149
00:09:09,789 --> 00:09:12,000
We'll tow it back
with us when we leave.

150
00:09:13,668 --> 00:09:16,087
What do you say
we get this done, sir.

151
00:09:21,718 --> 00:09:23,595
[KODAI]
Hard to know which way to go.

152
00:09:23,678 --> 00:09:24,929
[SANADA]
Indeed.

153
00:09:25,013 --> 00:09:27,390
[MORI] X.O. Didn't you say
an alien civilization

154
00:09:27,474 --> 00:09:29,726
older than the Gamilans
built this gate?

155
00:09:29,809 --> 00:09:31,019
[SANADA]
We think so.

156
00:09:31,102 --> 00:09:32,604
They would be horrified.

157
00:09:32,687 --> 00:09:35,732
The Gamilans took a beautiful
thing and they tainted it.

158
00:09:35,815 --> 00:09:37,942
Well, "The sorrow
of being tainted

159
00:09:38,026 --> 00:09:40,653
makes the snow fall
once more." Yes?

160
00:09:40,737 --> 00:09:41,654
What's that?

161
00:09:41,738 --> 00:09:43,698
It's by Chuya Nakahara.

162
00:09:43,782 --> 00:09:46,993
I used to know someone who
was obsessed with that poem.

163
00:09:47,077 --> 00:09:49,829
It's a classic. From the
twentieth century, right?

164
00:09:49,913 --> 00:09:52,874
A poem from 200 years ago, huh?

165
00:09:52,957 --> 00:09:56,503
--Uh. Hey, wait a minute!
--Uh, what's wrong?

166
00:09:56,586 --> 00:09:58,254
Do you really think
the Iscandarians would know

167
00:09:58,338 --> 00:10:00,757
about this
Nakahara guy's poetry?

168
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:02,550
[KODAI]
He's ancient. Why would they?

169
00:10:02,634 --> 00:10:05,095
And if Iscandarians
don't know about him...

170
00:10:05,178 --> 00:10:07,347
[MORI gasps]

171
00:10:07,430 --> 00:10:09,182
Be quiet!

172
00:10:28,910 --> 00:10:31,538
Looks like they left
their guard dog behind.

173
00:10:31,621 --> 00:10:35,083
That may not be
the only one. This way.

174
00:10:36,876 --> 00:10:39,546
[NIIMI] He was always like
a guiding star for me.

175
00:10:39,629 --> 00:10:43,133
Whenever I didn't know what
to do, he'd point the way.

176
00:10:45,427 --> 00:10:47,595
[NIIMI] Here are those
papers you requested.

177
00:10:47,679 --> 00:10:50,390
Thank you.

178
00:10:50,473 --> 00:10:54,477
Hm. Word is the alien fleet
is on the outskirts of Mars

179
00:10:54,561 --> 00:10:57,105
and could reach orbit
any moment now.

180
00:10:57,188 --> 00:10:58,857
Yes, I heard that, too.

181
00:10:58,940 --> 00:11:00,650
Apparently they've
upgraded the shelters

182
00:11:00,734 --> 00:11:02,110
from the Inner Planet War.

183
00:11:02,193 --> 00:11:05,405
And now the entire surface
is being evacuated.

184
00:11:05,488 --> 00:11:06,448
[door knob clicks]

185
00:11:06,531 --> 00:11:08,783
[MAMORU KODAI]
Don't worry.

186
00:11:08,867 --> 00:11:10,410
[NIIMI]
Kodai?

187
00:11:10,493 --> 00:11:12,829
Our side's about to launch
a big operation at Mars

188
00:11:12,912 --> 00:11:15,373
to show those invaders
who they're messing with.

189
00:11:15,457 --> 00:11:17,375
And where did you
hear that from?

190
00:11:17,459 --> 00:11:19,044
I can't say.

191
00:11:19,127 --> 00:11:22,422
[sighs]
So, what are you doing here?

192
00:11:22,505 --> 00:11:24,132
It's against regulation
for anyone to be

193
00:11:24,215 --> 00:11:26,134
in this lab without approval.

194
00:11:26,217 --> 00:11:28,261
And do <i>you</i> have
approval, Niimi?

195
00:11:28,345 --> 00:11:32,015
That's different. I'm bringing
Sanada materials he asked for.

196
00:11:32,098 --> 00:11:33,266
[SANADA chuckles]

197
00:11:33,350 --> 00:11:35,226
Yeah, so am I.

198
00:11:35,310 --> 00:11:36,853
--Here.
--[SANADA] Hm?

199
00:11:36,936 --> 00:11:40,065
You said you'd like to
check it out sometime, remember?

200
00:11:40,148 --> 00:11:42,359
A book of poems? Really?

201
00:11:42,442 --> 00:11:43,777
That's right.

202
00:11:43,860 --> 00:11:46,237
All this time I thought
he only cared about equations!

203
00:11:46,321 --> 00:11:49,741
Hm. I mean, don't be rude!

204
00:11:49,824 --> 00:11:53,119
I don't mean to cut this short,
but you've got a visitor.

205
00:11:53,203 --> 00:11:55,872
[MAMORU KODAI] Oh, yeah!
I promised I'd meet my brother!

206
00:11:55,955 --> 00:11:58,291
Bye.

207
00:11:58,375 --> 00:12:00,210
He does whatever he wants.

208
00:12:00,293 --> 00:12:02,796
Because he's honest
with himself, Niimi.

209
00:12:02,879 --> 00:12:05,965
You know, you could learn
a thing or two from him.

210
00:12:15,016 --> 00:12:16,851
Mamoru.

211
00:12:19,771 --> 00:12:22,565
Being more honest
with ourselves, huh?

212
00:12:22,649 --> 00:12:24,359
[KODAI]
This is great!

213
00:12:24,442 --> 00:12:27,070
I'm glad I was able
to prove you're an Earthling!

214
00:12:27,153 --> 00:12:29,572
It's the only way
to explain it, right?

215
00:12:29,656 --> 00:12:31,991
But-- then, what about
my amnesia--

216
00:12:32,075 --> 00:12:34,285
not remembering anything
beyond that year?

217
00:12:34,369 --> 00:12:36,663
Can it really be just a
coincidence that I lost

218
00:12:36,746 --> 00:12:39,541
my memory the same time
Yurisha disappeared?

219
00:12:39,624 --> 00:12:41,835
--[KODAI] Well.
--[SANADA] No, it's not.

220
00:12:43,378 --> 00:12:46,715
We should have told you
the truth from the start.

221
00:12:46,798 --> 00:12:51,344
You and Yurisha were together.
Victims of the same crash.

222
00:12:51,428 --> 00:12:54,806
Maybe it was an accident,
or maybe an act of terror.

223
00:12:54,889 --> 00:12:57,183
The investigators
could never say.

224
00:12:57,267 --> 00:12:59,310
All we know is
there was an explosion,

225
00:12:59,394 --> 00:13:01,312
and you lost your memory.

226
00:13:01,396 --> 00:13:03,606
And Yurisha fell into a coma.

227
00:13:05,692 --> 00:13:08,153
We had the best doctors
in the world working on her,

228
00:13:08,236 --> 00:13:10,363
but she never woke up.

229
00:13:10,447 --> 00:13:12,741
[KODAI]
Why didn't you tell us that?

230
00:13:12,824 --> 00:13:15,827
We know Iscandar is in the
Large Magellanic Cloud galaxy,

231
00:13:15,910 --> 00:13:17,746
but we don't know exactly where.

232
00:13:17,829 --> 00:13:18,955
[KODAI, MORI gasp]

233
00:13:19,039 --> 00:13:20,790
What? But aren't the
coordinates on the map?

234
00:13:20,874 --> 00:13:22,042
Yeah, that's right.

235
00:13:22,125 --> 00:13:23,668
You entered the data
in the Auto-Nav,

236
00:13:23,752 --> 00:13:25,628
and that's what it's using
to point us there.

237
00:13:25,712 --> 00:13:28,006
--It wasn't on the map.
--[KODAI, MORI gasp]

238
00:13:28,089 --> 00:13:30,258
She said she would reveal
"the path to Iscandar" to us

239
00:13:30,342 --> 00:13:32,719
as we journeyed.
Or that was the plan.

240
00:13:32,802 --> 00:13:34,137
[KODAI]
W-Wait a minute!

241
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:36,431
Then what's the
Auto-Nav been using?

242
00:13:36,514 --> 00:13:38,808
We've been following
Yurisha's memories.

243
00:13:38,892 --> 00:13:41,728
Her what? You don't mean that.

244
00:13:41,811 --> 00:13:45,732
[SANADA] Mm. The core of the
Automatic Navigation System

245
00:13:45,815 --> 00:13:46,983
is Yurisha herself.

246
00:13:47,067 --> 00:13:48,485
[BOTH gasp]

247
00:13:56,868 --> 00:13:59,412
[SANADA] We've been physically
tapping into her brain

248
00:13:59,496 --> 00:14:01,414
to point the way to Iscandar.

249
00:14:01,498 --> 00:14:02,582
[MORI]
But, sir.

250
00:14:02,665 --> 00:14:04,542
[SANADA]
I know it's ethically wrong,

251
00:14:04,626 --> 00:14:05,960
and we have to take
responsibility

252
00:14:06,044 --> 00:14:07,462
for what's happened.

253
00:14:07,545 --> 00:14:09,422
That's why we're going to take
her back home to Iscandar,

254
00:14:09,506 --> 00:14:12,425
where she can hopefully get
the help she needs to recover.

255
00:14:12,509 --> 00:14:14,886
That's a key element
of the <i>Yamato</i> 's mission.

256
00:14:14,969 --> 00:14:18,056
But sir, what about
Yurisha's message capsule?

257
00:14:18,139 --> 00:14:19,891
Why do I have it?

258
00:14:19,974 --> 00:14:21,142
The truth is...

259
00:14:21,226 --> 00:14:22,727
[KODAI yells]

260
00:14:28,566 --> 00:14:30,068
[SANADA]
Nice shooting.

261
00:14:30,151 --> 00:14:32,570
Now let's get inside
while we can.

262
00:14:32,654 --> 00:14:33,863
[KODAI]
Inside what?

263
00:14:33,947 --> 00:14:35,907
That should be a chamber door.

264
00:14:35,990 --> 00:14:39,285
It leads to the system
satellite's control area.

265
00:14:42,497 --> 00:14:47,502
♪

266
00:14:55,260 --> 00:14:56,886
At least the door works.

267
00:14:56,970 --> 00:14:59,597
I should be able to handle
the rest of it myself.

268
00:14:59,681 --> 00:15:01,391
You two wait for me here.

269
00:15:08,189 --> 00:15:09,774
[MORI gasps]

270
00:15:13,695 --> 00:15:14,946
[KODAI]
X.O! Hey!

271
00:15:15,030 --> 00:15:19,117
[beeping]

272
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,618
[KODAI]
X.O!

273
00:15:20,702 --> 00:15:22,287
[SANADA]
Just as I thought.

274
00:15:22,370 --> 00:15:24,164
If I reboot the
system satellite,

275
00:15:24,247 --> 00:15:27,042
then the subspace gate
should open automatically.

276
00:15:28,793 --> 00:15:30,211
[gasps]

277
00:15:34,382 --> 00:15:36,051
It's been locked
from the inside.

278
00:15:36,134 --> 00:15:37,427
[KODAI gasps]

279
00:15:37,510 --> 00:15:39,346
[SANADA]
Kodai, listen to me.

280
00:15:39,429 --> 00:15:41,181
To use the gate,
we need to reboot the system,

281
00:15:41,264 --> 00:15:43,350
but there's a catch.
Doing so is going to cause

282
00:15:43,433 --> 00:15:45,560
a massive neutron burst
in this chamber.

283
00:15:45,643 --> 00:15:47,354
--[MORI] Huh?
--[KODAI] But, sir.

284
00:15:47,437 --> 00:15:50,023
[SANADA] The door and walls
in here are specially shielded.

285
00:15:50,106 --> 00:15:53,318
So there's no need to worry.
You'll be safe out there.

286
00:15:53,401 --> 00:15:54,903
But what about you, sir?

287
00:15:54,986 --> 00:15:58,406
Is that terminal shielded,
or are you gonna be exposed?

288
00:15:59,366 --> 00:16:00,825
What are you planning to do?

289
00:16:00,909 --> 00:16:02,619
[MORI]
You can't, sir! It's suicide!

290
00:16:02,702 --> 00:16:04,662
No! Please don't do this!

291
00:16:04,746 --> 00:16:06,956
I'll see if I can
override the lock!

292
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:09,042
[KODAI]
Sanada, open the door!

293
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:13,421
Kodai. Listen. I told you
I used to know someone

294
00:16:13,505 --> 00:16:16,591
who loved Chuya Nakahara's
poetry, right?

295
00:16:16,675 --> 00:16:19,552
It was my friend, Mamoru.

296
00:16:19,636 --> 00:16:23,014
That's right.
Mamoru Kodai. Your brother.

297
00:16:23,098 --> 00:16:26,142
[KODAI] Wait, what? You and
my brother were friends?

298
00:16:26,226 --> 00:16:29,145
Yes. Best friends, in fact.

299
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,525
[door knob clicks]

300
00:16:33,608 --> 00:16:35,652
If you're looking
for Niimi, she left.

301
00:16:35,735 --> 00:16:37,278
Another meteorite.

302
00:16:37,362 --> 00:16:39,989
This one landed
on Rio de Janeiro.

303
00:16:40,073 --> 00:16:41,533
Clearly, the enemy
is launching them

304
00:16:41,616 --> 00:16:43,326
as catastrophic weapons.

305
00:16:43,410 --> 00:16:46,246
After Mars, the aliens have
changed their strategy.

306
00:16:48,164 --> 00:16:51,668
Hey, you want to go get some
actual fresh air for a change?

307
00:16:51,751 --> 00:16:53,378
Huh?

308
00:16:55,839 --> 00:16:57,924
[MAMORU KODAI]
Sky looks terrible.

309
00:16:58,008 --> 00:17:01,052
It could be the beginning
of a nuclear winter.

310
00:17:01,136 --> 00:17:02,554
Are you still planning to enlist

311
00:17:02,637 --> 00:17:04,305
in the Cosmo Navy
when you graduate?

312
00:17:04,389 --> 00:17:06,057
Yeah. And you?

313
00:17:06,141 --> 00:17:10,395
Not sure. I don't think
I'm cut out for the military.

314
00:17:10,478 --> 00:17:12,731
That said, there's got to be
something I can do

315
00:17:12,814 --> 00:17:16,484
to help us in this war.
That's all there is now.

316
00:17:16,568 --> 00:17:18,653
You'll find your true calling.

317
00:17:18,737 --> 00:17:20,363
You'll end up helping
the cause in a way

318
00:17:20,447 --> 00:17:23,283
I could never dream of.
That's my bet.

319
00:17:23,366 --> 00:17:26,870
A poem and an equation.
That's what we are.

320
00:17:26,953 --> 00:17:28,246
[SANADA]
Hm?

321
00:17:28,329 --> 00:17:30,165
[MAMORU KODAI]
We can bring order to this world

322
00:17:30,248 --> 00:17:32,000
in completely different ways.

323
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:34,544
But in the end,
our intentions are the same.

324
00:17:36,004 --> 00:17:38,256
Yeah.

325
00:17:38,340 --> 00:17:41,968
Chuya wrote, "The sorrow
of being tainted..."

326
00:17:42,052 --> 00:17:44,971
"...causes the snow
to fall once more."

327
00:17:45,055 --> 00:17:46,514
[KODAI]
Sanada!

328
00:17:46,598 --> 00:17:49,476
He's the best friend I ever had,
but I sent him to his death.

329
00:17:49,559 --> 00:17:51,603
[KODAI gasps]

330
00:17:51,686 --> 00:17:56,024
[SANADA] I couldn't tell him
that Operation M was a decoy.

331
00:17:56,107 --> 00:17:58,777
That the whole fleet was a decoy

332
00:17:58,860 --> 00:18:01,905
to get the Wave Motion Core.

333
00:18:01,988 --> 00:18:03,698
[YUKIKAZE PA VOICE 17A]
The operation will begin today

334
00:18:03,782 --> 00:18:04,949
as scheduled at...

335
00:18:05,033 --> 00:18:06,743
Well, good luck, Captain.

336
00:18:06,826 --> 00:18:08,161
[YUKIKAZE PA VOICE 17A]
...loading procedures for

337
00:18:08,244 --> 00:18:09,788
prototype torpedoes.

338
00:18:09,871 --> 00:18:11,373
[MAMORU KODAI]
We're launching this morning.

339
00:18:11,456 --> 00:18:12,665
--[SANADA] Mm.
--[MAMORU KODAI] I don't know

340
00:18:12,749 --> 00:18:15,043
how many ships
are gonna make it through.

341
00:18:15,126 --> 00:18:18,713
But we'll shut down their Pluto
base, no matter what it takes.

342
00:18:18,797 --> 00:18:21,132
[SANADA]
Did you get to see Niimi?

343
00:18:22,467 --> 00:18:25,261
No, we broke up. Real shame.

344
00:18:25,345 --> 00:18:26,930
[SANADA]
I see.

345
00:18:28,473 --> 00:18:31,184
Here, I never got a chance
to bring this back to you.

346
00:18:31,267 --> 00:18:35,146
You keep it. Please.
You need it more than I do.

347
00:18:35,230 --> 00:18:37,565
[SANADA] I've read it twice.
And I still don't understand

348
00:18:37,649 --> 00:18:39,484
why anyone likes poetry.

349
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:41,611
Wow, tell me what
you really think!

350
00:18:41,695 --> 00:18:43,113
[SANADA]
Hm.

351
00:18:43,780 --> 00:18:48,785
♪

352
00:19:07,137 --> 00:19:09,806
[SANADA] The fact it was
a decoy was top secret.

353
00:19:11,474 --> 00:19:14,144
I didn't have the courage
to tell my friend.

354
00:19:14,227 --> 00:19:16,771
I just obeyed my orders.

355
00:19:18,148 --> 00:19:20,859
That tells you
what kind of a man I am.

356
00:19:24,112 --> 00:19:25,739
Even if he had known
he was a decoy,

357
00:19:25,822 --> 00:19:29,659
it wouldn't have mattered.
He still would've gone.

358
00:19:29,743 --> 00:19:31,953
No matter the odds,
or how unreasonable the order,

359
00:19:32,037 --> 00:19:34,706
he would've believed
he could find a way.

360
00:19:34,789 --> 00:19:38,126
That's just how my brother was.

361
00:19:38,209 --> 00:19:41,755
Yes, you're right.
That does sound like him.

362
00:19:41,838 --> 00:19:44,090
Kodai. Your brother
would be proud

363
00:19:44,174 --> 00:19:46,134
that you've followed
in his footsteps.

364
00:19:46,217 --> 00:19:48,386
Sanada. What else?

365
00:19:48,470 --> 00:19:50,764
Keep talking, I didn't even
know he liked poetry!

366
00:19:50,847 --> 00:19:52,515
I'm almost in.

367
00:19:52,599 --> 00:19:57,062
[SANADA] "The sorrow of being
tainted longs for nothing.

368
00:19:57,145 --> 00:19:59,147
At dusk the sun
can do nothing more,

369
00:19:59,230 --> 00:20:02,734
and sets helplessly with
the sadness of being tainted."

370
00:20:03,777 --> 00:20:04,986
Sanada, wait!

371
00:20:05,070 --> 00:20:07,364
Please, tell me what made
my brother happy!

372
00:20:07,447 --> 00:20:10,116
What made him sad?
Just talk to me!

373
00:20:19,542 --> 00:20:22,545
Neutrons have flooded
the control room, Kodai.

374
00:20:22,629 --> 00:20:25,465
He couldn't survive that.
Nobody could.

375
00:20:27,133 --> 00:20:28,885
Sanada!

376
00:20:33,264 --> 00:20:36,893
[MISAKI]
The door is open. This is it.

377
00:20:36,976 --> 00:20:40,021
This is the path that leads
to the mother world.

378
00:20:40,814 --> 00:20:41,898
[beeping]

379
00:20:41,981 --> 00:20:43,400
[MORI gasps]

380
00:20:46,986 --> 00:20:48,238
Where is he?

381
00:20:48,321 --> 00:20:50,156
[KODAI]
No! Sanada!

382
00:20:55,286 --> 00:20:58,373
There's so much more
I wanted to know.

383
00:20:58,456 --> 00:21:02,127
I wanted to learn more
about my brother.

384
00:21:02,210 --> 00:21:04,629
And more about you.

385
00:21:10,343 --> 00:21:12,345
You're alive.

386
00:21:12,429 --> 00:21:15,473
Neutrons don't pass through
water so easily, Lieutenant.

387
00:21:15,557 --> 00:21:19,436
[gasps]
Honestly, sir,

388
00:21:19,519 --> 00:21:21,646
you amaze me.

389
00:21:50,759 --> 00:21:52,761
[OKITA]
Attention all crew:

390
00:21:52,844 --> 00:21:56,389
The gate is now online.

391
00:21:56,473 --> 00:21:58,391
Very soon, the <i>Yamato</i>
will be warping

392
00:21:58,475 --> 00:22:01,603
30,000 light-years
closer to our goal.

393
00:22:01,686 --> 00:22:03,813
But first, I need to
make something clear.

394
00:22:03,897 --> 00:22:07,025
Something I should have
said at the start.

395
00:22:07,108 --> 00:22:09,694
There is a rumor circulating
about an Iscandarian

396
00:22:09,778 --> 00:22:13,531
aboard this ship.
That much is true.

397
00:22:13,615 --> 00:22:17,077
But make no mistake,
she is not a crewmember.

398
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:20,872
She is in a coma in the
automatic navigation room.

399
00:22:26,711 --> 00:22:30,590
[MORI] So, I guess
you're Yurisha Iscandar.

400
00:22:30,674 --> 00:22:34,636
[MISAKI]
Actually, that would be me.

401
00:22:34,719 --> 00:22:39,349
Greetings friend.
I am Yurisha of Iscandar.

